The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of binary weights is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses implementation details for speeding up the generated models, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
